Female genitalia (
Figs 58–59
). Tergum VIII trapezoid. Papillae anales with setae at the distal area, approximately three times taller than longer, sclerotized at the basal half. Sternum VIII not fused with the lamella antevaginalis. Corpus bursae completely membranous, with paired signa located ventrally; ductus bursae about same length as the corpus bursae, anterior portion sclerotized and dilated.

Distribution (
Fig. 62
). This species is currently known only from the Atlantic province (Parana dominion), Bahia state, Brazil , between 200–1,000m altitude.
